xed) to verify correctness across scenarios.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The output is identical whether the changes being analyzed are staged or unstaged.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure is that the tool might use different git commands or logic for staged vs unstaged changes (e.g., incorrectly using `git diff --cached` for one but not the other, or vice versa). Real git staging state must be used to verify the tool produces consistent output regardless of staging. Mocking git output at different stages could hide inconsistencies in how the tool queries or processes staged vs unstaged data.","test_description":"Create a real git repository with a committed base state. Create one file change and stage it, create another file change and leave it unstaged. Run the tool and capture the output. Then reset and reorder (stage the second, leave first unstaged). Run the tool again and verify: (1) both outputs contain the same set of files and counts, (2) the report structure and counts are identical regardless of which changes are staged, and (3) the tool does not differentiate between staged and unstaged in its output.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.05}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13428,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13428},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"506266a8-4cd5-46d9-b4cf-e45d6e39f8a4","uuid":"6ba689d7-958f-4d7b-b1e0-143cfa66f3e7"}
